issue_obverse_figure_tesim: Right profile of Kawad II on frontal bust
issue_obverse_figure_description_tesim: crown with two mural elements, crescent above forehead; crescent, above covered korymbos; ribbon commencing to the left below crescent, pointing to the left; double pearl diadem, diadem ribbons commencing to the left and right behind the shoulders; pointing upwards; earing consisting of three elements; neck-line of tunica edged with row of pearls; in the middle medallion with three pendants; crescent on left and right shoulder; both shoulders decorated with crescent and star; double row of pearls running from the shoulders to the breast, star in left and right upper field; crescent at 3 h, 6 h and 9 h; dotted border
issue_obverse_legend_tesim: 2 h l. i. kw’t, 11 h l. o. pylwcy| Kawād Pērōz| “Kawad, the victorious”
issue_reverse_figure_description_tesim: base consisting of three elements, altar shaft, to the left and the right of the shaft ribbons hanging downwards; four altar slabs; altar flames rendered as four tiers of four, three, two and one strokes respectively; star to left of altar flames, crescent to the right; to the left and the right of the altar attendant with stylized crown of Kawad II, holding sword with both hands, right hand above left hand, both figures frontal; regnal year at 9 h; ; crescent at 3 h, 6 h 9 h and 12 h; dotted border
